com.atakmap.coremap.maps.coords

Class MGRSPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.coremap.maps.coords.MGRSPoint
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MutableMGRSPoint

    public class MGRSPoint
extends java.lang.Object
    Military Grid Reference System point. Currently only UTM subset is supported, but UPS will come if needed (implementation is left open for it). MGRS is only valid for latitude values ranging from -80 < x < 84. If the value falls outside of this range UPS will need to be used.

      • decodeString

        public static MGRSPoint decodeString(java.lang.String mgrsString,
                                     Ellipsoid geoRef,
                                     MutableMGRSPoint out)
        Parse a valid MGRS String into the appropriate MGRS point. A NumberFormatException may be trown if an invalid mgrsString is passed in. Examples of valid MRGS coordinates would be 4QFJ12345678 or 04QFJ12345678.
        Parameters:
        mgrsString - in the appropriate format of grid zone designator square identifier and then easting and northing.
        geoRef - can be Ellipsoid.WGS_84
        out - can be null.

      • decode

                               java.lang.String easting,

                               Ellipsoid geoRef,
                               MutableMGRSPoint out)
        Given a zone, sqare, easting and northing produce a MGRSPoint object. If the provided information is syntactically invalid then decode will return null.
